properties.Title: Heat Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: High temperatures and humidity are expected over much of southern and western Nova Scotia through Wednesday. Time span: continuing into Wednesday evening. Maximum daytime temperatures: near 29 degrees Celsius, except cooler along parts of the coast. Minimum nighttime temperatures: near 16 degrees Celsius. Locations: southern and western Nova Scotia. Remarks: Maximum temperatures on Wednesday will once again reach warning criteria over southern and western portions of the province. Although humidex values will be in the low 30s on Thursday, maximum temperatures are expected to reach only the mid 20s, and this warning is likely to be ended late Wednesday in these areas. ### Extreme heat affects everyone. Heat warnings are issued when very high temperature or humidity conditions are expected to pose an elevated risk of heat illnesses, such as heat stroke or heat exhaustion. Information is provided on the Nova Scotia Department of Health and Wellness website at https://novascotia.ca/heat-related-illness/. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NSstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NSStorm.

properties.Title: Update For The High Water Level Emergency Advisory Alert Issued By The Water Security Agency.
properties.Summary:
Description: Update for the High Water Level Emergency Advisory Alert issued by the Saskatchewan Water Security Agency. The water levels are still extremely high in many water systems in the far north. Logs, debris, unstable banks and other obstacles that may not normally be encountered are creating safety hazards for water travel. These high water levels are being closely monitored and residents should avoid the water and be exercising extreme caution when accessing water systems if travel is necessary.

properties.Title: Police Officer Stabbed In Bridgewater, Nova Scotia, Suspect At Large
properties.Summary:
Description: Man at large after stabbing a Bridgewater Police officer in Bridgewater, Nova Scotia. The weapon has not been recovered. He was last seen in wooded areas and back yards near the south edge of town approximately 4 hours ago. Police and RCMP have been actively searching for the suspect. He is wearing shorts with no shoes or shirt. If you see any suspicious persons or activity call the police.

properties.Title: Heat Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: High temperatures and humidity are expected over much of southern and western Nova Scotia through Wednesday. Time span: continuing into Wednesday evening. Maximum daytime temperatures: 27 to 30 degrees Celsius, except cooler along parts of the coast. Minimum nighttime temperatures: near 15 degrees Celsius. Locations: parts of mainland Nova Scotia. Remarks: Maximum temperatures on Wednesday will once again reach warning criteria over southern and western portions of the province. Although humidex values will be in the low 30s on Thursday, maximum temperatures are expected to reach only the mid 20s, and this warning is likely to be ended late Wednesday in these areas. Conditions will improve over eastern Nova Scotia, Kings County, and Hants County this evening, with cool overnight lows near 14 degrees giving some relief from the heat. This warning will be ended for these areas later this evening as temperatures begin to fall. ### Extreme heat affects everyone. Heat warnings are issued when very high temperature or humidity conditions are expected to pose an elevated risk of heat illnesses, such as heat stroke or heat exhaustion. Information is provided on the Nova Scotia Department of Health and Wellness website at https://novascotia.ca/heat-related-illness/.
